# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
# pygbag runs CPython in WebAssembly and needs SharedArrayBuffer, which the
# browser only exposes to a cross-origin-isolated page. These headers turn that
# isolation on; without them the game fails to boot.
#
# COEP must be `credentialless`, not `require-corp`: pygbag pulls the CPython
# interpreter and runtime from the cross-origin pygame-web.github.io CDN, which
# serves them with `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` but no Cross-Origin-Resource-
# Policy header. Under `require-corp` the browser blocks those loads
# (ERR_BLOCKED_BY_RESPONSE...COEP) and the game hangs on "Loading, please wait".
# `credentialless` still grants cross-origin isolation but lets public CDN
# resources load without a CORP header.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
